\sqrt{A^2 + B^2} = \sqrt{(1)^2 + (-2)^2} = \sqrt{5}
\dfrac{1}{\sqrt{5}} x - \dfrac{2}{\sqrt{5}} y = -\dfrac{-3}{\sqrt{5}}
\cos(\alpha)~x + \sin(\alpha)y = p \rightarrow \dfrac{1}{\sqrt{5}} x - \dfrac{2}{\sqrt{5}} y = -\dfrac{-3}{\sqrt{5}}
